Description: Up for grabs is this beautiful blond Strat with some cool upgrades. Neck is a 2002 20th Anniversary Standard Squier in flamed maple with a thick rosewood slab fretboard. Frets have been leveled, crowned and polished, action is low and fast, no buzz. Genuine bone nut. Fender Vintage style split shaft Gold Tuners, USA Fender Roller String Trees.Fender and Custom Shop logos added for fun and authenticity, they've been cleared and sealed, and look perfect. Neck is finished with nitrocellulose slightly aged for a vintage look and feel. Neck is straight, truss rod works correctly. Slim C profile. Body is one piece basswood, in near perfect shape, one very small ding on the back that is hard to see, but no major dents, scratches, etc. Gold vintage style bridge with Fender stamped saddles, gold input jack plate. Pickups are Alnico V Duncan Designed SC-101, very vintage tone with some extra bite, excellent Strat quack and chime. All electronics work as they should. Very vintage look, sound, feel and vibe, without the vintage price tag! Set up and intonated with fresh D'Addario XL10s. No issues, ready to rock ! This Strat will blow away any MIM Strat out there. No case, but I pack very securely and ship FAST! Check my feedback as a seller, players love my guitars, so buy with confidence, this is an amazing guitar for the $!!
Title: Fender/Squier Vintage Modified Stratocaster w/upgrades Near MINT!
